verses.text_plain: And the Lord said unto Noah, Come thou and all thy house into the ark; for thee have I seen righteous before me in this generation.
verses.verse_html: 1And the Lord said unto Noah, Come thou and all thy house into the ark; for thee have I seen righteous before me in this generation.

verses.text_plain: Of every clean beast thou shalt take to thee by sevens, the male and his female: and of beasts that are not clean by two, the male and his female.
verses.verse_html:
2Of every clean beast thou shalt take to thee by sevens, the male and his female: and of beasts that are not clean by two, the male and his female. ▼
▼ by sevens: Heb. seven seven

footnotes.body_html: ▼ by sevens: Heb. seven seven

verses.text_plain: Of fowls also of the air by sevens, the male and the female; to keep seed alive upon the face of all the earth.
verses.verse_html:
3Of fowls also of the air by sevens, the male and the female; to keep seed alive upon the face of all the earth. ▼
▼ by sevens: Heb. seven seven

footnotes.body_html: ▼ by sevens: Heb. seven seven

verses.text_plain: For yet seven days, and I will cause it to rain upon the earth forty days and forty nights; and every living substance that I have made will I destroy from off the face of the earth.
verses.verse_html:
4For yet seven days, and I will cause it to rain upon the earth forty days and forty nights; and every living substance that I have made will I destroy from off the face of the earth. ▼
▼ destroy: Heb. blot out

tokens.text: and I will cause it to rain

footnotes.body_html: ▼ destroy: Heb. blot out

verses.text_plain: And Noah did according unto all that the Lord commanded him.
verses.verse_html: 5And Noah did according unto all that the Lord commanded him.

tokens.text: according unto all that the Lord

verses.text_plain: And Noah was six hundred years old when the flood of waters was upon the earth.
verses.verse_html: 6And Noah was six hundred years old when the flood of waters was upon the earth.

verses.text_plain: And Noah went in, and his sons, and his wife, and his sons’ wives with him, into the ark, because of the waters of the flood.
verses.verse_html: 7And Noah went in, and his sons, and his wife, and his sons’ wives with him, into the ark, because of the waters of the flood.

verses.text_plain: Of clean beasts, and of beasts that are not clean, and of fowls, and of every thing that creepeth upon the earth,
verses.verse_html: 8Of clean beasts, and of beasts that are not clean, and of fowls, and of every thing that creepeth upon the earth,

tokens.text: and of every thing that creepeth

verses.text_plain: There went in two and two unto Noah into the ark, the male and the female, as God had commanded Noah.
verses.verse_html: 9There went in two and two unto Noah into the ark, the male and the female, as God had commanded Noah.

verses.text_plain: And it came to pass after seven days, that the waters of the flood were upon the earth.
verses.verse_html:
10And it came to pass after seven days, that the waters of the flood were upon the earth. ▼
▼ after…: or, on the seventh day

tokens.text: And it came to pass after seven

footnotes.body_text: ▼ after…: or, on the seventh day
footnotes.body_html: ▼ after…: or, on the seventh day

verses.text_plain: In the six hundredth year of Noah’s life, in the second month, the seventeenth day of the month, the same day were all the fountains of the great deep broken up, and the windows of heaven were opened.
verses.verse_html:
11In the six hundredth year of Noah’s life, in the second month, the seventeenth day of the month, the same day were all the fountains of the great deep broken up, and the windows of heaven were opened. ▼
▼ windows: or, floodgates

verses.text_plain: And the rain was upon the earth forty days and forty nights.
verses.verse_html: 12And the rain was upon the earth forty days and forty nights.

verses.text_plain: In the selfsame day entered Noah, and Shem, and Ham, and Japheth, the sons of Noah, and Noah’s wife, and the three wives of his sons with them, into the ark;
verses.verse_html: 13In the selfsame day entered Noah, and Shem, and Ham, and Japheth, the sons of Noah, and Noah’s wife, and the three wives of his sons with them, into the ark;

verses.text_plain: They, and every beast after his kind, and all the cattle after their kind, and every creeping thing that creepeth upon the earth after his kind, and every fowl after his kind, every bird of every sort.
verses.verse_html:
14They, and every beast after his kind, and all the cattle after their kind, and every creeping thing that creepeth upon the earth after his kind, and every fowl after his kind, every bird of every sort. ▼
▼ sort: Heb. wing

verses.text_plain: And they went in unto Noah into the ark, two and two of all flesh, wherein is the breath of life.
verses.verse_html: 15And they went in unto Noah into the ark, two and two of all flesh, wherein is the breath of life.

verses.text_plain: And they that went in, went in male and female of all flesh, as God had commanded him: and the Lord shut him in.
verses.verse_html: 16And they that went in, went in male and female of all flesh, as God had commanded him: and the Lord shut him in.

verses.text_plain: And the flood was forty days upon the earth; and the waters increased, and bare up the ark, and it was lift up above the earth.
verses.verse_html: 17And the flood was forty days upon the earth; and the waters increased, and bare up the ark, and it was lift up above the earth.

verses.text_plain: And the waters prevailed, and were increased greatly upon the earth; and the ark went upon the face of the waters.
verses.verse_html: 18And the waters prevailed, and were increased greatly upon the earth; and the ark went upon the face of the waters.

verses.text_plain: And the waters prevailed exceedingly upon the earth; and all the high hills, that were under the whole heaven, were covered.
verses.verse_html: 19And the waters prevailed exceedingly upon the earth; and all the high hills, that were under the whole heaven, were covered.

verses.text_plain: Fifteen cubits upward did the waters prevail; and the mountains were covered.
verses.verse_html: 20Fifteen cubits upward did the waters prevail; and the mountains were covered.

verses.text_plain: And all flesh died that moved upon the earth, both of fowl, and of cattle, and of beast, and of every creeping thing that creepeth upon the earth, and every man:
verses.verse_html: 21And all flesh died that moved upon the earth, both of fowl, and of cattle, and of beast, and of every creeping thing that creepeth upon the earth, and every man:

verses.text_plain: All in whose nostrils was the breath of life, of all that was in the dry land, died.
verses.verse_html:
22All in whose nostrils was the breath of life, of all that was in the dry land, died. ▼
▼ the breath…: Heb. the breath of the spirit of life

footnotes.body_text: ▼ the breath…: Heb. the breath of the spirit of life
footnotes.body_html: ▼ the breath…: Heb. the breath of the spirit of life

verses.text_plain: And every living substance was destroyed which was upon the face of the ground, both man, and cattle, and the creeping things, and the fowl of the heaven; and they were destroyed from the earth: and Noah only remained alive, and they that were with him in the ark.
verses.verse_html: 23And every living substance was destroyed which was upon the face of the ground, both man, and cattle, and the creeping things, and the fowl of the heaven; and they were destroyed from the earth: and Noah only remained alive, and they that were with him in the ark.

verses.text_plain: And the waters prevailed upon the earth an hundred and fifty days.
verses.verse_html: 24And the waters prevailed upon the earth an hundred and fifty days.
